{"content":"Divide into 6 equal portions (approx. 120 g each) and shape into a ball. Make a shallow indent in the centre of each ball with your thumb. Place 1½ tablespoons of almond mixture into indent. Pull edges of dough together to enclose filling, pinch to seal and reshape into a ball. Using a rolling pin, roll each ball, into an oval (approx. 22 cm long)."},{"content":"Set a plate aside. Place a large frying pan over high heat. Working 1 naan at a time, place into frying pan and cook until dark brown blisters form (approx. 1-1½ minutes each side). Remove naan from heat and place onto the plate. Then brush with ghee and sprinkle with extra coconut (optional). Transfer onto a serving dish and cover to keep warm. Repeat frying, brushing and sprinkling with remaining naan. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own ghee, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","Baked naans can be frozen. Allow to cool and store in a freezable bag or container, layered between pieces of baking paper. Defrost thoroughly before reheating in a hot oven (220°C). Place the naan on a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) lined with baking paper and sprinkle with a little water and heat until warmed through (approx. 5 minutes)."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}